title: THE BOYS Season 2 Episode 6 Breakdown, Wild Theories, and Details You Missed!
author: Think Story
comment: Hit me in the DMs for that special Think Story Love Sausage content. What do you think of these wild theories? I'm second guessing my Stormfront/Homelander mom one since the projector in the flashback with him was from the 2000s, meaning he could have grown up quicker than most kids. Anywho, leave a comment!
Anthony starr is perfect as homelander. He's just non-intentionally funny and impatient, a perfect psychopath.
Theory: Edgar is actually Frederick Vought. He just did a Get out on a black man

My favorite line in the whole episode was Homelander saying he was going to go run lines with Noire. It was such a small throw away line but hilarious. Just goes to show the amazing dialogue this series has.
I feel bad for Queen Maeve. You know by the end of the season,  somebody's gonna die.
description:
In this video we take a deep dive, breakdown, recap, review, and explain episode 6 of Amazon's THE BOYS Season 2! We'll discuss Stormfront's true origin, her relationship with Homelander, and former member of the seven, Lamplighter.
